elements.Text: Bachelor of Technology, Computer Science and Engineering
Worked in the development of the World’s first commercialized MCPTT solution on Android, based on 3GPP’s MCX communication standard, developed for first responders.
Contributed to the MCData component of the solution, adding the location altitude feature and messaging feature as per 3GPP and custom specifications respectively.

Responsibilities: Designing and developing specification-accurate solution, Collaborating with respective teams in Samsung HQ, South Korea for proper implementation and functioning, Testing and Integration activities, Debugging and resolution of possible issues.
Tech Stack: Android Studio, Java, C++, NodeJS, Perforce.
Worked with the Enterprise Infrastructure(EI) Business Unit to create an efficient Self-Service system for handling of the team’s Change creation process.
Researched ways to authenticate the smartphone user after the initial check using mobile sensors and Deep learning models (entry-point authentication).
Developed an Android application, SilentObserver, as a part of the project for experiments and as proof of concept.
Tech Stack: Java, Android, Django, Firebase, SQLite.
Classified the network traffic as malicious or benign using the Reinforcement learning algorithm (Deep Q-Network).
Compared its result with other supervised learning classifiers such as Logistic Regression, Neural Networks, Decision trees classifier.
Part of football fraternity of N.S.O. as a player.
Worked as a volunteer for organising Sangram 2018.
Technical: Java, Android Studio, C++, Python, NodeJS, Perforce, GitHub, Postman, MySQL.
Interests: Video Games, Football, Books, Movies, Technology.
